We offer e-learning training for all our employees, particularly employees working on activities  with  greater  exposure to  compliance  risks,  as  well  as the  members  of  our Board of Executive Officers and our Board of Directors.

In 2020, we offered training on the Code of Ethical Conduct to approximately 42,000 employees, in order to present the main aspects of the document. From July 31 through September 30, 2020, we undertook a campaign aiming to have all employees sign the term in which they declare that they have knowledge of the Code of Ethical Conduct's content, when we reached a rate of 98.5% of total employees who have signed the acknowledgement term.

